> Ruth Padriga\n\n*Writer:\nMacoy Infante<br>Daphne Catsao<br>Joeben Elpedes<br>Iman Manoguid<br>Audrey Delizo\n\n*Researcher:                       \nOrosa Jacinto<br>Julus Enoch Fechalin<br>Angelica Santos\n}}\n}}\n'''''Magandang Buhay''''' ({{Literal translation|''Beautiful Life''}}) is a [[Philippines|Philippine]] [[Breakfast television|morning]] [[talk show]] broadcast by [[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]]. The program premiered on April 18, 2016,<ref name=\"MagandangBuhayTeaser\">{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vZMTVdJfujM|title=Magandang Buhay Hosts Teaser: Starting April 18 on ABS-CBN!|publisher=ABS-CBN Entertainment|website=YouTube|date=May 11, 2016}}</ref> and currently airs every weekday mornings from 8:00{{nbsp}}AM to 9:30{{nbsp}}AM on the network's ''Umaganda'' morning block. It also airs worldwide via [[The Filipino Channel|TFC]]. An [[Encore|encore telecast]] is currently airing on [[Jeepney TV]] every weekday afternoons from 4:05{{nbsp}}PM to 5:10{{nbsp}}PM.\n\nThe show's title is inspired from the former popular line of the same name from the drama series ''[[Dream Dad]]''.<ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wf4k9N8BluI|title=Magandang Buhay: Beauty Gonzalez reunites with Jana Agoncillo|publisher=ABS-CBN Entertainment|website=YouTube|date=May 11, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n''Magandang Buhay'' premiered on April 18, 2016 at 7:30{{nbsp}}AM, replacing the defunct morning talk show ''[[Kris TV]]''. The program is hosted by [[Karla Estrada]], [[Melai Cantiveros]], and [[Jolina Magdangal]] .<ref name=\"MagandangBuhayTeaser\"/>\n\nOn June 21, 2016, the show moved to its new timeslot at 8:00{{nbsp}}AM.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://balita.net.ph/2016/06/20/magandang-buhay-binago-ang-time-slot/|title=Magandang Buhay, binago ang time slot|publisher=balita.net.ph|date=June 20, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Hosts==\n\n===Main===\n*[[Jolina Magdangal]]\n*[[Melai Cantiveros|Melai Cantiveros-Francisco]] \n*[[Karla Estrada]]\n\n===Occasional Guest hosts===\n*[[Bianca Gonzalez]]\n*[[Cristine Reyes]]\n*[[Dimples Romana]]\n*[[Kris Aquino]]\n\n==Pre-emptions==\n''Magandang Buhay'' is interrupted in some provinces via ABS-CBN Regional Network Group. The 9:30{{nbsp}}AM timeslot is used to air an afternoon program pre-empted by a provincial ''[[TV Patrol#TV Patrol on ABS-CBN Regional Network Group|TV Patrol Regional]]'' newscast. During the coverage of [[NBA]] on ABS-CBN every year, ''Magandang Buhay'' is either pre-empted or reduced to sixty minutes. The program can be also pre-empted to give way for special live coverages of international beauty pageants, presidential/midterm elections, and many more.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|https://entertainment.abs-cbn.com/tv/shows/magandangbuhay/main}}\n\n{{ABS-CBN Shows (current and upcoming)}}\n{{ABS-CBN talk shows}}\n\n[[Category:ABS-CBN shows]]\n[[Category:Philippine television talk shows]]\n[[Category:2016 Philippine television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Breakfast television in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Filipino-language television programs]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Magandang Buhay\n| show_name_2              = \n| image                    = Magandang Buhay-titlecard.jpg\n| caption                  = Title card\n| genre                    = [[Talk show]]\n| presenter                = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Karla Estrada]]\n* [[Melai Cantiveros|Melai Cantiveros-Francisco]]\n* [[Jolina Magdangal]]\n}}\n| developer                = {{Plainlist|\n* Lui Andrada\n* Macie Imperial\n* Evelyn Raymundo\n* Rachel Simon-Palomar\n}}\n| director                 = {{Plainlist|\n* Arnel Natividad\n* Pinggoy Generoso\n* Jon Raymund Moll\n* Rico Guerrero\n* Erick Salud\n* Jay Mendoza\n* Jose Mari Reyes\n\n}}\n| creator                  = Ian Reyno\n| producer                 = <nowiki>{{Plainlist|</nowiki>\n*Business Unit Head:\nJasmin Pallera\n\n*Execuvite Producer:\nAJ Rase\n\n*Associate Producers:\nAngel Marco\nMikee Albarillo\nKayla Pontigon\n| location                 = Studio 9, [[ABS-CBN Broadcasting Center]], [[Diliman]], [[Quezon City]]\n| opentheme                = \"Magandang Buhay\" by Karla Estrada, Melai Cantiveros and Jolina Magdangal\n| theme_music_composer     = Jonathan Manalo\n| country                  = [[Philippines]]\n| language                 = [[Filipino language|Filipino]]\n| num_episodes             = 907 <!--as of September 27, 2019-->\n| company                  = \n| runtime                  = 90 minutes\n| camera                   = [[Multiple-camera setup]]\n| channel                  = [[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]]\n| picture_format           = [[480i]] ([[Standard-definition television|SDTV]]) <br> [[1080i]] ([[High-definition television|HDTV]])\n| first_aired              = {{start date|2016|4|18}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| preceded_by              = ''[[Kris TV]]''\n| website                  = https://magandangbuhay.abs-cbn.com\n| head writer              = \n| writer                   = {{Plainlist|\n*Head Writer:\nDarla Sauler <br> Ruth Padriga\n\n*Writer:\nMacoy Infante<br>Daphne Catsao<br>Joeben Elpedes<br>Iman Manoguid<br>Audrey Delizo\n\n*Researcher:                       \nOrosa Jacinto<br>Julus Enoch Fechalin<br>Angelica Santos\n}}\n}}\n'''''Magandang Buhay''''' ({{Literal translation|''Beautiful Life''}}) is a [[Philippines|Philippine]] [[Breakfast television|morning]] [[talk show]] broadcast by [[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]]. The program premiered on April 18, 2016,<ref name=\"MagandangBuhayTeaser\">{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vZMTVdJfujM|title=Magandang Buhay Hosts Teaser: Starting April 18 on ABS-CBN!|publisher=ABS-CBN Entertainment|website=YouTube|date=May 11, 2016}}</ref> and currently airs every weekday mornings from 8:00{{nbsp}}AM to 9:30{{nbsp}}AM on the network's ''Umaganda'' morning block. It also airs worldwide via [[The Filipino Channel|TFC]]. An [[Encore|encore telecast]] is currently airing on [[Jeepney TV]] every weekday afternoons from 4:05{{nbsp}}PM to 5:10{{nbsp}}PM.\n\nThe show's title is inspired from the former popular line of the same name from the drama series ''[[Dream Dad]]''.<ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wf4k9N8BluI|title=Magandang Buhay: Beauty Gonzalez reunites with Jana Agoncillo|publisher=ABS-CBN Entertainment|website=YouTube|date=May 11, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n''Magandang Buhay'' premiered on April 18, 2016 at 7:30{{nbsp}}AM, replacing the defunct morning talk show ''[[Kris TV]]''. The program is hosted by [[Karla Estrada]], [[Melai Cantiveros]], and [[Jolina Magdangal]] .<ref name=\"MagandangBuhayTeaser\"/>\n\nOn June 21, 2016, the show moved to its new timeslot at 8:00{{nbsp}}AM.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://balita.net.ph/2016/06/20/magandang-buhay-binago-ang-time-slot/|title=Magandang Buhay, binago ang time slot|publisher=balita.net.ph|date=June 20, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Hosts==\n\n===Main===\n*[[Jolina Magdangal]]\n*[[Melai Cantiveros|Melai Cantiveros-Francisco]] \n*[[Karla Estrada]]\n\n===Occasional Guest hosts===\n*[[Bianca Gonzalez]]\n*[[Cristine Reyes]]\n*[[Dimples Romana]]\n*[[Kris Aquino]]\n\n==Pre-emptions==\n''Magandang Buhay'' is interrupted in some provinces via ABS-CBN Regional Network Group. The 9:30{{nbsp}}AM timeslot is used to air an afternoon program pre-empted by a provincial ''[[TV Patrol#TV Patrol on ABS-CBN Regional Network Group|TV Patrol Regional]]'' newscast. During the coverage of [[NBA]] on ABS-CBN every year, ''Magandang Buhay'' is either pre-empted or reduced to sixty minutes. The program can be also pre-empted to give way for special live coverages of international beauty pageants, presidential/midterm elections, and many more.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|https://entertainment.abs-cbn.com/tv/shows/magandangbuhay/main}}\n\n{{ABS-CBN Shows (current and upcoming)}}\n{{ABS-CBN talk shows}}\n\n[